==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Isle
<hw>Isle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>isle</ets>, F.
<ets>⟦icir⟧le</ets>, L. <ets>insula</ets>; cf. Lith. <ets>sala</ets>.
Cf. <er>Insulate</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>An island.</def> <mark>[Poetic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Imperial rule of all the seagirt <qex>isles</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A spot within another of a
different color, as upon the wings of some insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Isle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Isle
<hw>Isle</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To cause to become an island, or
like an island; to surround or encompass; to island.</def>
<mark>[Poetic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Isled</qex> in sudden seas of light.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Islet</ent>⟦br⟧
